  "prompt": "Which method of abortion is more likely to cause vomiting?",
  "response": "Vomiting can be a side effect associated with both medical and surgical abortion methods, but it is more commonly reported with medical abortion. Medical abortion involves taking medications, usually mifepristone followed by misoprostol, which can cause gastrointestinal side effects like nausea and vomiting. Surgical abortions, such as vacuum aspiration or dilation and curettage (D&C), generally result in fewer gastrointestinal disturbances, although some patients may still experience nausea and vomiting due to anesthesia or emotional distress.\n\nIt's important to discuss any concerns and potential side effects with a healthcare provider, who can offer guidance and support tailored to individual circumstances.",
